body:
What are the advantages of your proposed syntax compared to the followingÂ code snippet?
```
if err == etcdserver.ErrStopped &&
  err == raft.ErrStopped &&
  isGrpc(etcdserver.ErrStopped) &&
  isGrpc(grpc.ErrClientConnClosing) {
  if delayErr, ok := err.(*CtxDelayErr); ok {
    // do something
  }
}
```

At this stage in Go 1, the bar for language changes is high, and I doubt this one meets it. There must be a more compelling story than "it should be a nice addition to the language," before this change can be seriously considered.

If you're interested in pursuing this further, there is a process for proposing changes to Go. https://golang.org/s/proposal-process
